# Laravel scheduling and Horizon

Register recurring tasks in [`bootstrap/app.php`](bootstrap/app.php) via `->withSchedule(function (Schedule $schedule) { ... })`. Do **not** use `Console\Kernel` for new schedulingâ€”Laravel 11+ uses `Application::configure()` and `withSchedule`. See [.cursor/rules/laravel.mdc](.cursor/rules/laravel.mdc) for the Laravel 12 application shell.

## `withoutOverlapping()` in `withSchedule`

- **Always** chain **`->withoutOverlapping(...)`** on every scheduled **`$schedule->job(...)`** or **`$schedule->command(...)`** in `bootstrap/app.php`. Pass **seconds** when the task can exceed the default mutex expiry (e.g. long backups: `->withoutOverlapping(7200)`).
- Omitting `withoutOverlapping()` for new schedule entries is **not** allowed.

## Recurring / scheduled work â†’ Job (Horizon)

- Put work in `app/Jobs/`, implement `ShouldQueue`, use `Dispatchable`, `InteractsWithQueue`, `Queueable`, `SerializesModels` as needed.
- Register with **`$schedule->job(YourJob::class)->daily()->withoutOverlapping()`** (or `hourly()`, `everyMinute()`, etc., **always** ending with `withoutOverlapping()`).
- **Do not** add new **cron-like** recurring logic as a scheduled Artisan commandâ€”use a job so it runs through the queue and appears in Horizon.

âś”
```php
$schedule->job(RenewNurserySubscriptionDatesJob::class)
    ->daily()
    ->withoutOverlapping();

$schedule->job(RunBackupJob::class)
    ->twiceDaily()
    ->withoutOverlapping(7200);
```

âś–
```php
$schedule->job(RenewNurserySubscriptionDatesJob::class)->daily();

$schedule->command('nursery:renew-subscriptions')->daily();
```

## When Artisan commands are OK

- One-off or manual CLIs (migrations, data fixes, deploy hooks): `app/Console/Commands/...` invoked by developers or scriptsâ€”not the default for **scheduled** background work.

## Queues and Horizon

- Most jobs: default queue (see [`config/horizon.php`](config/horizon.php) `default` supervisor).
- Long-running or backup-related jobs: `public $queue = 'backups';` so they use the `backups` supervisor (higher timeout/memory).
- Set `$tries`, `$timeout`, and `$backoff` on jobs when failure/retry behavior matters.

